Edited:
[1]  - 2015/03/10

++ Pros
+ Awesome gameplay;
+ Good variety of weapons and levels;
+ Beautiful graphics;
+ Guaranteed fun (if your settings allow to play at low ping and your have enough friends to play with).
+ Edit [1]: Added local multiplayer gaming option with controllers, but limited to 4 players. Still no LAN multiplayer.
+ Edit [1]: It seems that the amount of players have increased just a bit, turning the game playable.

-- Cons
- Classic online-gaming sync problem: http://www.polygon.com/2014/3/11/5491146/why-you-dont-want-an-online-mode-towerfall
- Small community (there are no enemies online to play against! You must invite your friends. Specially if your server is Japan or Asia);
- No LAN gaming option, like Terraria (Port-forwarding, Peer-to-peer);
- Seems not optimized, unnecessarily slow for what is actually running.

Final impression:
I recommend to buy it at 50%+ discount, because it is still not worth paying the whole price, since the cons are too strong (especially the 3rd con" I listed: no LAN). If they fix this issue
